Those who have inquired about step by step instructions… here it is 😀 Thanks for all the appreciation 😇

Check out other reel for full video 🤙🏻
Step 1: Find center where you want to mount your TV/sound bar
Step 2 : Prepare a frame where you will hang your MDF board panel ( I used 2x4x8 Pine wood)
Step 3: add strip lights on the frame
Step 4 : add slats either side of the wall ( 1x2x8 pine wood with wood glue & Nail gun)
Step 5: for slats : finish it with wood filler, sand it and paint it. 
Step 6: attach MDF board (1/2x4x8) to the frame with a cut out for your TV wall mount and wires). I used one and half as per my dimension
Step 7: Prime and Paint your MDF board
Step 8: Mount your TV
Step 9: Mount/Place TV console (mine from @povisonhome) as you like

10ft light Tree outside your house is highlight in just under $50.  I have transformed a curtain light from last year into a 10ft light tree with a star topper. Quick DIY.

You need below items - link in Bio
1. Curtain light - $20 from @costco 
2. Tree Topper - $15 From @target 
3. PVC pipe - $5 from @homedepot 
4. U Pins - $5 from @amazon 
5. Few screws

Let me know in comments if you need link of any materials. Happy DIY.

Mystery Box 😃🏈🏎️

Inspired by @onehandymomma 

List of material & steps to build this Mystery Box
Material
1. 3/4 inch Plywood
2. 2.5” screws
3. Drill
4. Kreg Jig for pocket holes
5. Tv lift mechanism-link in Bio
6. TV (I used 50”)
7. Paint - your choice of color
8. Wheels - link in bio

Cut list
1. Front & Back 2 - 46 x 33.5”
2. Sides 2 - 34 x 11.5”
3. Bottom 1 - 46 x 11.5”
4. Top Lid 1 - 48 x 12-1/4
